HEADWORD: Psychometry
<hw>Psy*chom"e*try</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Psycho-</ets> + <ets>-metry</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>The art of measuring the duration of mental
processes, or of determining the time relations of mental
phenomena.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Psy`cho*met"ric</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

